{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9abc1eee-b424-4b73-bd1b-d78ff0280da9","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by #1234\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\n> **Note:** In xUnit, `Skip` is a property on `[Fact]`/`[Theory]`, not a separate attribute. All other frameworks use a standalone attribute alongside the test marker.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0e084c27-fdfd-443e-8a4e-1718504b3a95","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":321,"requestId":"0421:2EB5E6:2051E4F:2443909:69E81E11"},"id":"c38c7798-4ec3-4457-abe6-74c1935d22de","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:02:51.291Z","parentId":"81cc0181-3fb3-4d64-b64b-89387f42c04a"}
